rdf:Description.dbpedia-owl:abstract: The British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) is a British public service broadcaster headquartered at Broadcasting House in the City of Westminster, London. It is the largest broadcaster in the world, with about 23,000 staff. Its main responsibility is to provide impartial public service broadcasting in the United Kingdom, Channel Islands and Isle of Man. The BBC is a semi-autonomous public service broadcaster that operates under a Royal Charter and a Licence and Agreement from the Home Secretary. Within the United Kingdom its work is funded principally by an annual television licence fee, which is charged to all British households, companies and organisations using any type of equipment to record and/or receive live television broadcasts; the level of the fee is set annually by the British Government and agreed by Parliament. Outside the UK, the BBC World Service has provided services by direct broadcasting and re-transmission contracts by sound radio since the inauguration of the BBC Empire Service in December 1932, and more recently by television and online. Though sharing some of the facilities of the domestic services, particularly for news and current affairs output, the World Service has a separate Managing Director, and its operating costs have historically been funded mainly by direct grants from the British government. These grants were determined independently of the domestic licence fee and were usually awarded from the budget of the Foreign and Commonwealth Office. As such, the BBC's international content has traditionally represented at least in part an effective foreign policy tool of the British Government. The recent BBC World Service spending review has announced plans for the funding for the world service to be drawn from the domestic licence fee. The Corporation's "guaranteed" income from the licence fee and the World Service grants are supplemented by profits from commercial operations through a wholly owned subsidiary, BBC Worldwide Ltd. The company's activities include programme- and format-sales, magazines including the Radio Times and book publishing. The BBC also earns additional income from selling certain programme-making services through BBC Studios and Post Production Ltd. , formerly BBC Resources Ltd, another wholly owned trading subsidiary of the corporation. The BBC is sometimes referred to as "Auntie" and "the Beeb". The former is also used to refer to the BBC's sister corporation, the Australian Broadcasting Corporation.

La British Broadcasting Corporation (Corporacin Britnica de Radiodifusin), ms conocida como BBC, es el servicio pblico de comunicacin del Reino Unido. Tiene su sede en la Broadcasting House en Westminster, Londres. Es el mayor grupo de comunicacin del mundo con cerca de 23.000 empleados. Sus funciones son las de retransmitir televisin y radio de forma pblica en el Reino Unido, la Isla de Man y las Islas del Canal. Es un ente pblico y autnomo establecido en 1922 por un Decreto Real que garantiza su independencia del control comercial y poltico. En el Reino Unido se financia mediante una licencia de televisin que paga cada hogar, compaa y organizacin en donde haya cualquier equipamiento capaz de recibir y/o grabar las emisiones de radio y televisin. El precio de esta licencia es fijado anualmente por el Gobierno britnico y acordado en el Parlamento. En 2010 el precio por hogar fue de 145.50. Fuera del Reino Unido opera bajo el indicativo de BBC World Service y su labor es la de retransmitir por radio y televisin todos sus productos y ms recientemente, tambin por internet. A pesar de compartir esctructuras, especialmente el servicio de noticias, el World Service opera independientemente y tiene un Director Ejecutivo propio. Se financia principalmente por fondos pblicos del Gobierno britnico, independientemente de la financiacin proveniente de la licencia de televisin. La otra fuente de financiacin de la Corporacin son mediante sus filiales comerciales, BBC Worldwide Ltd. (venta de programas y formatos, publicacin de revistas y libros) y por el alquiler de sus estudios de televisin, organizados en la filial BBC Studios and Post Production Ltd. (anteriormente BBC Resources Ltd.).

rdf:Description.dbpedia-owl:abstract: La British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) fonde en 1922 est un organe de production et de diffusion de programmes de radio-tlvision britannique. Ayant son sige au Royaume-Uni, cest un non-departmental public body en charge des mdia. La BBC bnficie dune rputation dexcellence culturelle, et est parfois affectueusement appele The Beeb ou Auntie (langage enfantin pour tante) par les Britanniques. Pendant longtemps, elle est reste la seule socit diffusant des programmes de tlvision et de radio au Royaume-Uni. Au dbut du XXIsicle, elle reoit environ 3,6milliards par anne et, pour la priode 2008-2009, ses revenus mondiaux ont t de 1milliard de dollars. Cest la plus puissante socit de diffusion au monde en termes de revenu brut et de tlspectateurs. Avant la venue de ITV (Independent Television) en 1955 et des radios locales prives dans les annes 1970, elle dtenait le monopole de diffusion.

British Broadcasting Corporation, mest kjent under forkortelsen BBC, er en britisk radio- og TV-kringkaster. I Storbritannia blir organisasjonen ofte kalt The Beeb eller Auntie ('tante', fordi den tidligere var kjent for ha en oppdragende stil i mange av sine programmer). Selskapet har omfattende egenproduksjon av programmer. BBC blir av mange oppfattet som et av de mest serise medieselskapene i verden, med en nytral og selvstendig synsvinkel. BBC ptar seg rollen som allmennkringkaster i Storbritannia, og det norske NRK, i likhet med de fleste andre eldre fjernsynskanaler i Europa, sammenligner seg derfor ofte med BBC. 2. november 1936 begynte BBC de frste regulre TV-sendingene i verden. Fr ITV ble opprettet i 1955 hadde BBC monopol p radio- og TV-sendinger i Storbritannia. BBC blir, p samme mte som NRK, finansiert med lisensmidler. Riktignok blir enkelte deler av BBCs programtilbud betalt av andre; for eksempel World Service, som blir betalt av det britiske utenriksdepartementet. Dessuten har BBC i de senere r tjent endel p sin kommersielle del, som har solgt DVD-kopier av deres store antall programmer. BBC blir, srlig etter opphevingen av monopolet, til stadighet kritisert for ikke ha en nytral innstilling. Srlig er det vanlig at det britiske regjeringspartiet klager p at de favoriserer opposisjonen; dette skjer uansett hvilket parti det er som sitter ved makten. Til tider har det kommet klager fra begge sider p ett og samme innslag, noe BBCs ledelse har tolket dithen at nytralitetskravet er oppfylt enten man fornrmer begge sider eller gleder begge sider. I 2004 ble BBCs ry for nytralitet skadet av Hutton-rapporten, som tok for seg skandalen omkring unyaktige rapporter om massedeleggelsesvpen i Irak etter David Kellys selvmord i 2003. Rapporten frte til at styreformannen og generaldirektren, samt en journalist, mtte si opp sine stillinger. BBC har i stor grad gjenopprettet tilliten, blant annet ved at de ansvarlige mtte g.

La British Broadcasting Corporation (Corporaci Britnica de Difusi), ms coneguda com a BBC, s la primera empresa de televisi i rdio del Regne Unit. A ms, s la ms gran de transmissi de notcies d'arreu del mn. Produeix serveis de programes i informaci, transmetent a la televisi, a la rdio i a Internet; sent una de les cadenes de notcies ms respectades del mn. s independent de controls comercials i poltics operant sota un estatut real que li garanteix la independncia. T una plantilla de 25.500 empleats i un pressupost anual de 4 bilions de . L'any 2004 fou guardonat amb el Premi Antonio Asensio de Periodisme.

rdf:Description.dbpedia-owl:abstract: De British Broadcasting Corporation, afgekort BBC, maar in de gesproken omgangstaal van het eigen land vaak aangeduid met de nickname Beeb, is de publieke omroep van het Verenigd Koninkrijk. De in 1922 opgerichte BBC is een van de oudste zendgemachtigden ter wereld. Programma's worden onder andere aangeboden via de televisiezenders BBC One, BBC Two, BBC Three, BBC Four, BBC Entertainment, BBC News 24 en BBC World, en via een aantal radiozenders waaronder BBC 1 t/m 7. De BBC World Service zendt programma's uit in meer dan 30 verschillende talen en wordt in de westerse wereld in het algemeen beschouwd als een gezaghebbende, objectieve nieuwsbron. De BBC zendt uit via grondstations, via satellieten en via het internet. De omroep wordt in eigen land voornamelijk gefinancierd uit kijk- en luistergeld en de opbrengsten van merchandising, televisie- en formatrechten, maar in het geheel niet uit reclame-inkomsten. In Nederland en Belgi zijn op de meeste kabelnetten de televisiestations BBC One, BBC Two en BBC World te ontvangen; de World Service op de radio wordt ook vaak via de kabel doorgegeven en zendt verder uit via korte golf en satelliet. Tot 2011 was de World Service in het grootste deel van Nederland, Belgi en Noord-Frankrijk ook op de middengolf te ontvangen. BBC Radio 4 is te ontvangen via de lange golf (198 kHz), en BBC Radio Five Live via de middengolf (693 en 909 kHz); verder ook via het internet, satelliet en sommige kabelnetten.
